{"questionId":"9072095","questionHtml":"<p>Deduce the equation for the relationship between absorbance and concentration.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/d049eab6fc4eafc2c797a23038c0448d127a9a90.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Slope (gradient):</em></p>\n<p>40 ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Equation:</em></p>\n<p>absorbance&nbsp;= 40 × concentration</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>y</em>&nbsp;= 40<em>x</em> ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept any correct relationship for slope such as <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1.00}}{{0.025}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.00</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.025</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</em></p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> if equation in M2 is correct.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072095","referenceCode":"18N.3.sl.TZ0.b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the equation for the relationship between absorbance and concentration.","paper":"3","level":"sl","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.2 Graphical techniques","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}